GCP Console → IAM & Admin → Organisation Policies
   → Search: iam.disableServiceAccountKeyCreation
   → Edit → Add Exception → Select your project
Option 2 — Use Workload Identity Federation (No Key Needed)
This is the modern, recommended alternative to JSON keys. It allows your pipeline to authenticate using short-lived tokens instead of a stored key file — actually more secure.

How it works: Instead of a JSON key file, the pipeline gets a temporary token from Google each time it runs. No secret file to store or protect.

