Since your org blocks JSON key creation, use OAuth — it takes about 5 minutes:

Step 1 — Create OAuth Client ID in GCP Console:

console.cloud.google.com
  → APIs & Services
    → Credentials
      → Create Credentials
        → OAuth 2.0 Client ID
          → Application type: Desktop App
          → Name: negd-pipeline-oauth
          → Click Create
          → Download JSON
Step 2 — Save the downloaded file:

Rename it → oauth_client_secret.json
Place at  → negd_pipeline/config/oauth_client_secret.json
Step 3 — Set in your .env file:

AUTH_METHOD=oauth
Step 4 — Run the pipeline once:

python pipeline.py --test-connections
A browser window opens → log in with your Google account → click Allow → done. The token is saved to config/token.pickle and every future run is fully automatic with no browser.

Key Difference Between the 4 Methods
Your Situation	Set AUTH_METHOD=
JSON key blocked by org (your case)	oauth
JSON key allowed	service_account
Running on GitHub Actions	workload_identity
Running on a GCP / NIC VM	vm_default
To run code, enable code execution and file creation in Settings > Capabilities.